**REITs / REAL ESTATE**

**INDUSTRY MODULE**

Supplemental Underwriting Guide

Version 2.1 \| January 2026

*Based on Empirical Analysis of 127 REIT Securities Cases*

*Including Orchid Island Capital (ORC) Case Study*

**EXECUTIVE SUMMARY**

REITs face MODERATE filing frequency but EXTREME subsector variation.
This module provides ACTIONABLE decision criteria with specific
thresholds and point adjustments.

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **NUCLEAR TRIGGERS - IMMEDIATE ESCALATION**                           |
|                                                                       |
| Active securities class action on Stanford SCAC                       |
|                                                                       |
| Non-traded REIT structure (suitability/NAV exposure)                  |
|                                                                       |
| AFFO payout ratio \>110% (dividend funded by debt/dilution)           |
|                                                                       |
| Office concentration \>70% in current market                          |
|                                                                       |
| Going concern opinion in most recent 10-K/10-Q                        |
|                                                                       |
| mREIT book value decline \>40% YoY                                    |
|                                                                       |
| Short seller report \<6 months (Hindenburg/Wolfpack)                  |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **KEY PROTECTIVE FACTORS**                                            |
|                                                                       |
| Data center / industrial focus with AI demand tailwind                |
|                                                                       |
| mREIT 100% Agency RMBS (government-guaranteed, zero credit risk)      |
|                                                                       |
| Internalized management (eliminates external manager conflicts)       |
|                                                                       |
| AFFO payout ratio \<85% with demonstrated dividend stability          |
|                                                                       |
| Zero or minimal long-term debt (eliminates refinancing risk)          |
|                                                                       |
| Clean Stanford SCAC and SEC Lit Releases (no prior suits)             |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

